  | first = 
  | authorlink = 
  | coauthors = 
  | title = Forensicare Orientation Handbook
  | publisher = VIFMH
  | date = May 2009
  | pages = 31}}</ref> sailed from England to [[South Australia]]; they then travelled across to [[Melbourne]].  The journey to Melbourne was not without incident and Embling was caught up in the bush fires of [[Black Thursday (1851)|Black Thursday]] in February 1851.<ref name=dictaustbiog>{{cite book
