==Death and commemoration==

Thomas Embling died of "Senile Debility" on 17 January 1893 survived by his wife and four children.<ref name=adb />

In April 2000 '[[Thomas Embling Hospital]]' was opened.  Built adjacent to the site of the original Yarra Bend Asylum, Thomas Embling Hospital is operated by the Victorian Institute of Forensic Mental Health and is a secure hospital for patients from the criminal justice system who are in need of psychiatric assessment, care and treatment.<ref>{{cite web
